message.content: Salvia mellifera is a species of woody perennial herb in the family Lamiaceae. It is a fragrant and aromatic flowering plant that is native to California. The leaves are a gray-green color and have a soft, velvety texture. The flowers grow in clusters on tall stems and are a vibrant shade of purplish-blue. The plant grows up to 6 feet in height and width. It is commonly used in landscaping and is also cultivated for its honey production. Salvia mellifera is drought-resistant and can be found in dry, sunny locations such as hillsides and chaparral communities.
